# New Relic MCP Server

Model Context Protocol (MCP) Server for seamless New Relic integration with Cursor IDE.

## Features
- Execute NRQL queries directly from Cursor
- Search and analyze New Relic logs
- Monitor applications and performance metrics
- Natural language query interface

## Quick Start
```bash
# 1. Configure credentials
cp config.env.example .env
# Edit .env with your New Relic credentials

# 2. Start the server
./run_mcp_docker.sh run

# 3. Configure Cursor with the displayed MCP configuration
# 4. Restart Cursor and start querying!
```

## Requirements
- Docker Desktop installed and running
- Valid New Relic API key and account access
- Cursor IDE with MCP support
